<p:sld xmlns:a="http://schemas.openxmlformats.org/drawingml/2006/main" xmlns:r="http://schemas.openxmlformats.org/officeDocument/2006/relationships" xmlns:p="http://schemas.openxmlformats.org/presentationml/2006/main"><p:cSld><p:bg><p:bgPr><a:solidFill><a:schemeClr val="accent3"/></a:solidFill><a:effectLst/></p:bgPr></p:bg><p:spTree><p:nvGrpSpPr><p:cNvPr id="1" name=""/><p:cNvGrpSpPr/><p:nvPr/></p:nvGrpSpPr><p:grpSpPr><a:xfrm><a:off x="0" y="0"/><a:ext cx="0" cy="0"/><a:chOff x="0" y="0"/><a:chExt cx="0" cy="0"/></a:xfrm></p:grpSpPr><p:sp><p:nvSpPr><p:cNvPr id="2" name="Title 1"><a:extLst><a:ext uri="{FF2B5EF4-FFF2-40B4-BE49-F238E27FC236}"><a16:creationId xmlns:a16="http://schemas.microsoft.com/office/drawing/2014/main" id="{8E1EC96A-5D68-9368-3652-147A54967E76}"/></a:ext></a:extLst></p:cNvPr><p:cNvSpPr><a:spLocks noGrp="1"/></p:cNvSpPr><p:nvPr><p:ph type="title"/></p:nvPr></p:nvSpPr><p:spPr/><p:txBody><a:bodyPr/><a:lstStyle/><a:p><a:endParaRPr lang="en-US"/></a:p></p:txBody></p:sp><p:sp><p:nvSpPr><p:cNvPr id="3" name="Content Placeholder 2"><a:extLst><a:ext uri="{FF2B5EF4-FFF2-40B4-BE49-F238E27FC236}"><a16:creationId xmlns:a16="http://schemas.microsoft.com/office/drawing/2014/main" id="{BFEF645D-66BE-A782-7881-39438E30B7CD}"/></a:ext></a:extLst></p:cNvPr><p:cNvSpPr><a:spLocks noGrp="1"/></p:cNvSpPr><p:nvPr><p:ph idx="1"/></p:nvPr></p:nvSpPr><p:spPr/><p:txBody><a:bodyPr><a:normAutofit fontScale="55000" lnSpcReduction="20000"/></a:bodyPr><a:lstStyle/><a:p><a:r><a:rPr lang="en-US" dirty="0"/><a:t>This is too test </a:t></a:r><a:r><a:rPr lang="en-US" dirty="0" err="1"/><a:t>scrom</a:t></a:r><a:r><a:rPr lang="en-US" dirty="0"/><a:t> engine </a:t></a:r><a:br><a:rPr lang="en-US" dirty="0"/></a:br><a:r><a:rPr lang="en-US" dirty="0"/><a:t>Please tell me the exact error message from your browser console (F12) or your Python terminal so we can trace the crash.</a:t></a:r></a:p><a:p><a:r><a:rPr lang="en-US" dirty="0"/><a:t>That is definitely a roadblock, but because we just rebuilt the export engine, the failure is likely happening for one of these specific reasons:</a:t></a:r></a:p><a:p><a:r><a:rPr lang="en-US" b="1" dirty="0"/><a:t>Payload Size Limit:</a:t></a:r><a:r><a:rPr lang="en-US" dirty="0"/><a:t> Because the new PPTX parser extracts images as raw Base64 text strings, a presentation with a lot of high-resolution images will create a massive JSON payload. When you click Export, sending 50MB+ of text back to the </a:t></a:r><a:r><a:rPr lang="en-US" dirty="0" err="1"/><a:t>FastAPI</a:t></a:r><a:r><a:rPr lang="en-US" dirty="0"/><a:t> server might be triggering a server limit or a timeout.</a:t></a:r></a:p><a:p><a:r><a:rPr lang="en-US" b="1" dirty="0"/><a:t>Missing Metadata:</a:t></a:r><a:r><a:rPr lang="en-US" dirty="0"/><a:t> If the PPTX parser grabbed a shape or placeholder that doesn't cleanly fit into our </a:t></a:r><a:r><a:rPr lang="en-US" dirty="0" err="1"/><a:t>CourseData</a:t></a:r><a:r><a:rPr lang="en-US" dirty="0"/><a:t> JSON structure, the backend might be rejecting the request with a 422 </a:t></a:r><a:r><a:rPr lang="en-US" dirty="0" err="1"/><a:t>Unprocessable</a:t></a:r><a:r><a:rPr lang="en-US" dirty="0"/><a:t> Entity error.</a:t></a:r></a:p><a:p><a:r><a:rPr lang="en-US" b="1" dirty="0"/><a:t>How to isolate this right now:</a:t></a:r><a:endParaRPr lang="en-US" dirty="0"/></a:p><a:p><a:r><a:rPr lang="en-US" b="1" dirty="0"/><a:t>If the UI says "Failed to export":</a:t></a:r><a:r><a:rPr lang="en-US" dirty="0"/><a:t> Press F12, go to the Console tab, and tell me what the red text says (e.g., Server Error 422 or Payload Too Large).</a:t></a:r></a:p><a:p><a:r><a:rPr lang="en-US" b="1" dirty="0"/><a:t>If it spins forever:</a:t></a:r><a:r><a:rPr lang="en-US" dirty="0"/><a:t> Check your Python terminal to see if it threw a 500 Internal Server Error or an Out of Memory warning.</a:t></a:r></a:p><a:p><a:r><a:rPr lang="en-US" b="1" dirty="0"/><a:t>If the ZIP downloads but the PPTX content is missing inside:</a:t></a:r><a:r><a:rPr lang="en-US" dirty="0"/><a:t> Let me know, as that means the Python HTML renderer is ignoring the specific way the PPTX blocks are formatted.</a:t></a:r></a:p><a:p><a:r><a:rPr lang="en-US" dirty="0"/><a:t>Paste whatever error you are seeing, and I will give you the exact fix.</a:t></a:r></a:p><a:p><a:endParaRPr lang="en-US" dirty="0"/></a:p><a:p><a:endParaRPr lang="en-US" dirty="0"/></a:p></p:txBody></p:sp></p:spTree><p:custDataLst><p:tags r:id="rId1"/></p:custDataLst><p:extLst><p:ext uri="{BB962C8B-B14F-4D97-AF65-F5344CB8AC3E}"><p14:creationId xmlns:p14="http://schemas.microsoft.com/office/powerpoint/2010/main" val="3027782891"/></p:ext></p:extLst></p:cSld><p:clrMapOvr><a:masterClrMapping/></p:clrMapOvr></p:sld>